## Overview
Explored DOM-based XSS where execution happens entirely in the browser.

## Key Concept
User input from the URL is inserted into the page via JavaScript.

## Scenario
Input was placed inside an HTML attribute:
<img src="USER_INPUT">

## Payload
"><svg onload=alert(1)>

## Steps
1. Identified source (location.search)
2. Found sink (HTML attribute via JS)
3. Broke out of attribute using "
4. Closed tag with >
5. Injected executable SVG payload

## Insight
DOM XSS often requires understanding how JavaScript manipulates the DOM and escaping the correct context.
